title: Jennette McCurdy is Glad Her Mom Died
description:
In one of the most anticipated memoirs of the year, Jennette McCurdy finally gets her time to slime the people that have silenced her for years. With captivating honesty Jennette walks us through how she got started in show business against her will and how she’s managed to finally break away and discover herself. 


Thanks Dipsea.  Get a 30 day free trial when you go to DipseaStories.com/worm.



Subscribe to our newsletter for weekly loose ends and misc. Thoughts!
